# Confidence: No public PoC known — pattern inferred from the CVE/advisory
# description only. The vulnerability is described as an information disclosure
# in Windows RDP (CVE-2026-56171) [1][2], exploitable over the network without
# special privileges [1], with a CVSS score of 7.1 (HIGH) [1].
#
# IMPORTANT LIMITATIONS:
# - No packet-capture (PCAP) data source is available to this pipeline —
#   this pattern is NOT verified against captured exploit traffic.
# - The advisory context retrieved from MSRC [2] was incomplete (JavaScript
#   required to render full advisory detail); no specific wire-level
#   indicators, affected protocol fields, or response payloads were
#   recoverable from source material.
# - The RDP content match below targets the standard RDP negotiation
#   sequence on TCP/3389 from external hosts. It is intentionally broad
#   and WILL produce false positives against legitimate RDP traffic.
# - This rule should be treated as a VISIBILITY/TRIAGE aid only. Do NOT
#   deploy in drop/reject mode without analyst validation against
#   environment-specific traffic baselines.
# - An analyst with access to full MSRC advisory detail [2] or vendor-
#   supplied indicators should refine or replace this pattern before
#   production use.
# - CVE-2026-56171 is 3 days old at time of rule generation; this rule
#   is a proposed draft for analyst review.

alert tcp $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET 3389 (
  msg:"THREATFORGE CVE-2026-56171 Windows RDP Information Disclosure attempt";
  flow:established,to_server;
  content:"|03 00|";
  depth:2;
  content:"|e0|";
  within:10;
  threshold:type both, track by_src, count 3, seconds 60;
  reference:cve,2026-56171;
  metadata:mitre_technique_id T1040, is_kev false, status experimental;
  classtype:attempted-recon;
  sid:9000004; rev:1; )

